        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-13T20:24:24.626Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Usually, the messages should still come through for about a month after the new version becomes available. The auto update not working could be for a variety of reasons. The first one that comes to mind would be a space issue. If there is not enough space available, the update stops. How much space do they have left? Are other apps still performing their auto updates?<br>\nWhich iOS version are they on? If it is very old, it could not longer be supported. Do manual updates still work for Signal?</p>",
